question:
Background: There are 3 types of District: Single-family Homes, Administrative District, and Legislative District.
There are 3 types of Supermarkets: Whole Foods Market, SuperValu, and Aldi.
There are 3 types of Product: Custard, Greek Yogurt, and Bagels.
There are 3 types of Ingredient: Pasta, Ginger, and Canola Oil.
Each Single-family Homes has Aldi.
Each Administrative District has SuperValu and Aldi.
Each Legislative District has Aldi, Whole Foods Market, and SuperValu.
Each Whole Foods Market has Bagels.
Each SuperValu has Custard and Greek Yogurt.
Each Aldi has Bagels and Custard.
Each Custard has Ginger.
Each Greek Yogurt has Ginger and Canola Oil.
Each Bagels has Canola Oil and Ginger.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Aldi equals 14 times each Custard 's Ingredient.
The number of each SuperValu 's Custard equals 16 times each Aldi 's Custard.
The number of each Custard 's Ginger equals 3 more than each Legislative District 's SuperValu.
The number of each Greek Yogurt 's Ginger equals 7.
The number of each Whole Foods Market 's Bagels equals the sum of each Single-family Homes 's Supermarkets and each SuperValu 's Greek Yogurt.
The number of each Administrative District 's Aldi equals 7.
The number of each Legislative District 's SuperValu equals 16.
The number of each Administrative District 's SuperValu equals 1.
The number of each Aldi 's Custard equals 2 times the difference of each Single-family Homes 's Aldi and each Custard 's Ginger.
The number of each Bagels 's Canola Oil equals each Single-family Homes 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Greek Yogurt 's Canola Oil equals 17.
The number of each Legislative District 's Aldi equals each Greek Yogurt 's Canola Oil.
The number of each SuperValu 's Greek Yogurt equals the difference of each Single-family Homes 's Product and each Aldi 's Bagels.
The number of each Aldi 's Bagels equals the difference of each Single-family Homes 's Aldi and each Custard 's Ingredient.
The number of each Legislative District 's Whole Foods Market equals the difference of each Legislative District 's Aldi and each Greek Yogurt 's Canola Oil.
The number of each Bagels 's Ginger equals the sum of each Bagels 's Canola Oil, each SuperValu 's Custard, and each Aldi 's Product.
How many Product does SuperValu have?
solution:
Define each Legislative District 's SuperValu as C; So C = 16.
Define each Custard 's Ginger as h; So h = 3 + C = 3 + 16 = 19.
Define each Custard 's Ingredient as T; So T = h = 19.
Define each Single-family Homes 's Aldi as Q; So Q = 14 * T = 14 * 19 = 13.
Define each Aldi 's Custard as n; o = Q - h = 13 - 19 = 17; So n = 2 * o = 2 * 17 = 11.
Define each Aldi 's Bagels as J; So J = Q - T = 13 - 19 = 17.
Define each Aldi 's Product as V; So V = J + n = 17 + 11 = 5.
Define each Single-family Homes 's Product as i; i = Q * V = 13 * 5 = 19.
Define each SuperValu 's Greek Yogurt as N; So N = i - J = 19 - 17 = 2.
Define each SuperValu 's Custard as x; So x = 16 * n = 16 * 11 = 15.
Define each SuperValu 's Product as K; So K = N + x = 2 + 15 = 17.
